Summers off...ha! More like a few weeks off before you hit the trainings, start classroom preparations, and begin lesson planning for the entire next year. Teacher Institute half days...if you mean teacher work days, ok. Those days are full of meetings, parent teacher conferences, and if you're lucky more lesson planning. Sick days and personal days...we got 5 altogether. Hope you have some saved up in case your own children get sick. Health insurance...laughable compared to other plans. There are benefits that teachers have, but it is no walk in the park as you are making it sound. You have no idea what you're talking about.
